WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.857 --> 00:00:02.595
Every story has a beginning.

2
00:00:03.973 --> 00:00:07.340
But ours... doesn't start
the way you might think.

3
00:00:07.833 --> 00:00:11.312
<i>Sure. it begins on a street
that looks like most</i>

4
00:00:11.437 --> 00:00:13.789
<i>and with a family that
was. for the most part.</i>

5
00:00:13.914 --> 00:00:16.182
<i>normal. average. ordinary.</i>

6
00:00:16.799 --> 00:00:19.727
<i>It was the morning I convinced
my wife Stephanie to turn</i>

7
00:00:19.895 --> 00:00:22.304
<i>her research trip into
a much-needed family vacation.</i>

8
00:00:22.429 --> 00:00:25.826
While your mom's working.
we'll be out and about exploring Belém.

9
00:00:26.118 --> 00:00:27.861
- Belém?
- It's in Brazil. sweetie.

10
00:00:28.029 --> 00:00:30.238
- Brazil?
- South America. dumb-ass.

11
00:00:30.832 --> 00:00:33.283
Why we have to go right now?
It's not a good time for me and Lucas.

12
00:00:33.451 --> 00:00:34.558
Not a good time?

13
00:00:34.683 --> 00:00:37.509
- You've only been dating for 2 weeks.
- When did you start dating Lucas Fisher?

14
00:00:37.634 --> 00:00:40.172
Just because you Twitter-spy me
doesn't mean that you know everything.

15
00:00:40.297 --> 00:00:43.084
When was the last time we did
something together as a family?

16
00:00:43.252 --> 00:00:45.042
Last month.
You forced us to play charades.

17
00:00:45.167 --> 00:00:47.870
and then you pulled out your back.
miming some scene from <i>Iron Man</i>.

18
00:00:47.995 --> 00:00:50.828
That was an old
sports injury I reaggravated.

19
00:00:50.953 --> 00:00:54.313
No. I mean. when was the last time
we did something as a family?

20
00:00:55.806 --> 00:00:57.348
Yellowstone. three years ago.

21
00:00:57.516 --> 00:01:00.603
- We all got poison Ivy.
- There's no poison Ivy in Brazil. kid.

22
00:01:01.920 --> 00:01:04.471
I just don't know why you
guys can't go without me. and then

23
00:01:04.596 --> 00:01:05.916
Photoshop me in later.

24
00:01:06.610 --> 00:01:07.907
We're all gonna go.

25
00:01:08.032 --> 00:01:10.320
and we're all gonna have
the time of our lives.

26
00:01:10.820 --> 00:01:14.445
Belém. Brazil

27
00:01:14.909 --> 00:01:17.165
That's the plane? Are you kidding?

28
00:01:17.290 --> 00:01:19.739
- It does look a little...
- Like a flying coffin.

29
00:01:19.864 --> 00:01:21.727
Come on. you guys.
Since we've been here.

30
00:01:21.852 --> 00:01:23.665
we have not done one thing together.

31
00:01:23.790 --> 00:01:26.827
You text. you work. and
you stare at the television.

32
00:01:26.952 --> 00:01:28.909
You gotta concentrate.
It's in South American.

33
00:01:29.034 --> 00:01:32.374
For one hour. we are going
to take a sunset tour

34
00:01:32.499 --> 00:01:33.593
 of the rainforest

35
00:01:33.761 --> 00:01:37.138
together as a family. because
that's how memories are made.

36
00:01:37.306 --> 00:01:39.681
whether you want them or not!

37
00:01:50.071 --> 00:01:52.520
Hey! The storm really
came out of nowhere. huh?

38
00:01:52.645 --> 00:01:55.317
Don't worry. I've flown
through much worse.

39
00:01:55.442 --> 00:01:56.762
Oh. yeah? When?

40
00:01:57.417 --> 00:01:59.628
Actually. I was just trying
to make you feel better.

41
00:01:59.753 --> 00:02:01.579
This is about as bad
as I've ever been up in.

42
00:02:03.916 --> 00:02:06.177
- Who are you texting now?
- God.

43
00:02:08.713 --> 00:02:10.830
- Where are your life vests?
- Back there!

44
00:02:11.733 --> 00:02:12.590
Hold on!

45
00:02:12.715 --> 00:02:14.032
It's okay. pussycat.

46
00:02:14.452 --> 00:02:16.452
- Are we gonna crash?
- Here.

47
00:02:17.596 --> 00:02:18.596
Okay. kid.

48
00:02:19.579 --> 00:02:21.140
just like space mountain. right?

49
00:02:21.308 --> 00:02:23.560
As soon as Mitch
gets us down safely. son.

50
00:02:23.685 --> 00:02:26.281
you'll be begging me
to go up again. I promise.

51
00:02:28.556 --> 00:02:30.149
That didn't happen
on space mountain.

52
00:02:30.662 --> 00:02:32.307
Mayday. mayday. mayday.

53
00:02:36.574 --> 00:02:39.000
Mom. I'm gonna die. and I
haven't even done it yet!

54
00:02:40.998 --> 00:02:43.621
Listen. listen. we're gonna
be all right. I promise!

55
00:02:44.109 --> 00:02:45.999
Have I ever lied to you before?

56
00:02:47.232 --> 00:02:49.836
- About anything this important?
- Yeah.

57
00:02:52.161 --> 00:02:53.324
Buckle up!

58
00:03:02.949 --> 00:03:03.799
Steph!

59
00:03:04.868 --> 00:03:05.710
Me. too.

60
00:03:06.270 --> 00:03:09.397
<i>At that moment. I couldn't help
wondering how my family got here...</i>

61
00:03:10.453 --> 00:03:11.537
<i>from here... </i>

62
00:03:12.526 --> 00:03:15.028
<i>a time that was.
quite simply. perfect.</i>

63
00:03:16.775 --> 00:03:18.536
And I had never been happier.

64
00:03:19.666 --> 00:03:21.524
<i>But if there is a downside
to your family</i>

65
00:03:21.649 --> 00:03:24.203
<i>being the center
of your entire world...</i>

66
00:03:24.371 --> 00:03:25.740
Toss the rock with dad?

67
00:03:25.865 --> 00:03:28.041
<i>It's that eventually.
all families grow up...</i>

68
00:03:28.209 --> 00:03:29.743
Wanna play some ball with daddy?

69
00:03:29.868 --> 00:03:30.906
<i>Grow apart.</i>

70
00:03:31.378 --> 00:03:33.536
<i>Stephanie barely had time to notice.</i>

71
00:03:33.920 --> 00:03:35.441
<i>Who could blame her?</i>

72
00:03:35.566 --> 00:03:38.377
<i>Her career as a research
scientist had taken off.</i>

73
00:03:38.502 --> 00:03:39.886
Executive vice president

74
00:03:40.054 --> 00:03:41.154
of research.

75
00:03:42.745 --> 00:03:44.314
<i>And I was happy for her.</i>

76
00:03:49.271 --> 00:03:50.521
<i>But I missed...</i>

77
00:03:51.059 --> 00:03:51.770
<i>us.</i>

78
00:03:52.675 --> 00:03:54.967
<i>We were all living under
the same roof. </i>

79
00:03:55.328 --> 00:03:56.876
<i>But in different worlds.</i>

80
00:03:58.026 --> 00:04:00.114
<i>And I was all alone in mine.</i>

81
00:04:02.117 --> 00:04:03.785
<i>So that's how we got here.</i>

82
00:04:04.225 --> 00:04:05.370
<i>And this... </i>

83
00:04:05.749 --> 00:04:07.410
<i>this was the beginning.</i>

84
00:04:12.975 --> 00:04:13.833
Hold on!

85
00:04:14.380 --> 00:04:15.380
Oh. my God!

86
00:04:16.257 --> 00:04:17.632
Brace for impact!

87
00:04:34.233 --> 00:04:34.978
Dad!

88
00:04:35.718 --> 00:04:36.508
Mom!

89
00:04:36.633 --> 00:04:38.580
<i>Fortunately. we all
survived. Jim. the pilot!</i>

90
00:04:38.705 --> 00:04:40.295
- Jim. the pilot!
- Mitch!

91
00:04:41.267 --> 00:04:44.180
<i>Unfortunately.
our pilot wasn't as lucky.</i>

92
00:04:45.804 --> 00:04:47.494
<i>We held each other close...</i>

93
00:04:50.290 --> 00:04:52.332
<i>Vowing a new beginning to things...</i>

94
00:04:53.453 --> 00:04:54.453
<i>Sincere...</i>

95
00:04:55.324 --> 00:04:56.874
<i>Heartfelt promises...</i>

96
00:05:02.992 --> 00:05:04.508
Just shoot me an e-mail.

97
00:05:04.633 --> 00:05:07.098
and I will see you first thing
in the morning. Bye.

98
00:05:08.467 --> 00:05:10.601
J.J.. remember. your
report's due tomorrow.

99
00:05:10.769 --> 00:05:13.338
and. Daphne. you need to
find your basketball uniform.

100
00:05:13.898 --> 00:05:14.698
Sorry.

101
00:05:16.147 --> 00:05:18.151
That was Katie from the lab.

102
00:05:19.477 --> 00:05:20.403
You okay?

103
00:05:20.571 --> 00:05:22.865
Guess it was crazy to think

104
00:05:23.276 --> 00:05:24.782
the trip would change anything.

105
00:05:26.391 --> 00:05:29.245
I know you want us to have
some great family moments. but...

106
00:05:30.082 --> 00:05:32.039
Come on. we survived
a plane crash together.

107
00:05:32.419 --> 00:05:34.584
Talk about a memory
that lasts a lifetime.

108
00:05:38.702 --> 00:05:40.447
Yeah. it's work. It can wait.

109
00:05:40.572 --> 00:05:42.175
How about dinner tomorrow night?

110
00:05:44.081 --> 00:05:46.328
No cell phones. No urgent e-mails.

111
00:05:46.453 --> 00:05:49.140
Just a nice bottle of wine
and a few hours to remind us.

112
00:05:50.153 --> 00:05:51.044
Of what?

113
00:05:51.428 --> 00:05:53.065
How great we are together.

114
00:05:59.129 --> 00:06:01.486
<i>Know what I was really thinking
when that plane was going down?</i>

115
00:06:01.654 --> 00:06:03.610
"I should have flown commercial"?

116
00:06:03.735 --> 00:06:05.269
The world needs her...

117
00:06:05.394 --> 00:06:08.123
I mean. who she is. what she does.

118
00:06:08.530 --> 00:06:10.577
I mean. Stephanie matters.
And me?

119
00:06:10.961 --> 00:06:12.047
Who am I?

120
00:06:12.592 --> 00:06:14.048
A failed painter?

121
00:06:14.364 --> 00:06:15.917
Ineffectual police artist?

122
00:06:16.085 --> 00:06:18.077
Guy who won't shut up
when I'm trying to hit?

123
00:06:18.202 --> 00:06:20.159
Look. have you tried...
radical idea...

124
00:06:20.284 --> 00:06:23.117
- just telling her how you feel?
- How are you supposed to tell someone

125
00:06:23.760 --> 00:06:25.656
that you've been
living separate lives?

126
00:06:25.781 --> 00:06:27.312
I am no expert on marriage.

127
00:06:27.437 --> 00:06:29.276
as my last two wives will attest.
but...

128
00:06:30.687 --> 00:06:31.511
here.

129
00:06:34.241 --> 00:06:36.227
- A divorce attorney?
- Oh. that's the wrong card.

130
00:06:36.352 --> 00:06:38.397
I'm sorry about that.
Sorry.

131
00:06:40.416 --> 00:06:41.804
Couple's therapist?

132
00:06:41.929 --> 00:06:43.953
Both my ex-wives
begged me to see him.

133
00:06:44.078 --> 00:06:46.656
That and hating me were the only
two things they had in common.

134
00:06:46.824 --> 00:06:48.125
Now had I listened.

135
00:06:48.475 --> 00:06:50.440
maybe I wouldn't
have needed this card.

136
00:06:51.027 --> 00:06:52.620
Maybe you won't either.

137
00:07:01.021 --> 00:07:03.131
<i>Ma'am. the more details you give me.</i>

138
00:07:03.256 --> 00:07:05.883
<i>- the better sketch I can draw.
- I don't see the point.</i>

139
00:07:06.051 --> 00:07:07.546
I already told the detectives

140
00:07:07.671 --> 00:07:09.793
I couldn't see his face.
He was wearing a mask.

141
00:07:09.918 --> 00:07:11.886
Of president Obama. I know.

142
00:07:12.011 --> 00:07:14.126
But if you can remember anything...

143
00:07:14.251 --> 00:07:15.764
hair color. eye color.

144
00:07:16.103 --> 00:07:17.562
See. I can create a composite

145
00:07:17.730 --> 00:07:19.480
which I can give to the detectives.

146
00:07:19.809 --> 00:07:22.011
Now it's not gonna
bring your husband back.

147
00:07:22.485 --> 00:07:24.277
but it might help
save somebody else's.

148
00:07:24.445 --> 00:07:27.395
We opened that jewelry store
with money from my father.

149
00:07:29.025 --> 00:07:30.616
Why don't we take a little break?

150
00:07:38.383 --> 00:07:39.250
Powell.

151
00:07:39.418 --> 00:07:40.251
Cho.

152
00:07:41.712 --> 00:07:43.011
Detective Cho.

153
00:07:47.563 --> 00:07:48.725
Day after day.

154
00:07:48.850 --> 00:07:51.550
facing people you know
you just can't help.

155
00:07:52.525 --> 00:07:53.800
How do you do it?

156
00:07:54.636 --> 00:07:56.690
By not asking myself that question.

157
00:07:58.694 --> 00:08:00.977
Crime's up.
It's as bad as I've seen it.

158
00:08:02.346 --> 00:08:04.400
Wish more people around here
cared as much as you do.

159
00:08:06.489 --> 00:08:07.737
Gun! Gun!

160
00:08:14.818 --> 00:08:16.951
- You all right?
- Yeah. You?

161
00:08:23.699 --> 00:08:25.421
The bullet... where'd it go?

162
00:08:27.257 --> 00:08:29.300
Hey. hey. You all right?

163
00:08:31.653 --> 00:08:33.763
I just need some fresh air.

164
00:08:51.365 --> 00:08:54.008
<i>No Ordinary People</i> presents...

165
00:08:54.133 --> 00:08:55.873
Season 1 episode 1
Pilot

166
00:08:55.998 --> 00:08:58.038
Akiha. Arsenic. delphiki. etig.

167
00:08:58.163 --> 00:09:00.748
Hellwerine. jeminicriquet.
qelul2. rohh2o

168
00:09:00.916 --> 00:09:02.240
www.u-sub.net

169
00:09:06.403 --> 00:09:09.943
In the morning. there's that second
just before you wake up

170
00:09:10.068 --> 00:09:13.470
when the world hasn't pressed
itself in on your chest.

171
00:09:14.006 --> 00:09:15.773
before you remember your work

172
00:09:15.898 --> 00:09:18.345
or the husband you
can't connect with

173
00:09:18.470 --> 00:09:20.823
or the kids you fear
you'll disappoint.

174
00:09:24.273 --> 00:09:27.973
But what I woke up to that morning
was something very different.

175
00:09:31.280 --> 00:09:34.108
What I woke up to was a
man i hadn't seen in years.

176
00:09:34.233 --> 00:09:35.915
Beautiful day?

177
00:09:39.009 --> 00:09:40.231
Want me to close this?

178
00:09:43.997 --> 00:09:46.503
I've been... Meaning to fix that.

179
00:09:47.811 --> 00:09:51.807
Though Jim seemed different.
i barely had time to wonder why.

180
00:09:52.426 --> 00:09:55.095
And truth is. I barely
had any time at all.

181
00:09:55.263 --> 00:09:59.070
Between work and home. there weren't
enough hours in the day.

182
00:09:59.195 --> 00:10:02.102
J.J.'S meets the counselor at 3:00.
but they might move it to 2:00

183
00:10:02.655 --> 00:10:04.854
Be on call just in case.

184
00:10:05.022 --> 00:10:07.023
Anybody who wants a ride. now we go.

185
00:10:08.067 --> 00:10:09.671
Eggs right here!

186
00:10:15.523 --> 00:10:17.283
I will see you later. J.J.

187
00:10:17.711 --> 00:10:18.508
Daph...

188
00:10:19.526 --> 00:10:20.495
Are you okay?

189
00:10:21.084 --> 00:10:22.956
I can tell there's
something on your mind.

190
00:10:23.574 --> 00:10:26.292
About Lucas or the plane crash?

191
00:10:26.625 --> 00:10:29.087
We had a near-death experience.
It's bound to change you.

192
00:10:29.480 --> 00:10:30.665
That whore!

193
00:10:33.739 --> 00:10:34.718
Or not.

194
00:10:35.822 --> 00:10:39.347
- Hi. baby. Excuse me.
- Daphne. you're back.

195
00:10:39.515 --> 00:10:41.393
Just in time. too. apparently.

196
00:10:41.518 --> 00:10:43.101
I'm glad that you survived.

197
00:10:43.329 --> 00:10:44.811
Memorial assemblies
are depressing.

198
00:10:44.979 --> 00:10:47.200
I know. I remember the
one we had for your virginity.

199
00:10:47.325 --> 00:10:49.107
What was it. like two years ago?

200
00:10:50.346 --> 00:10:51.235
See ya.

201
00:10:51.697 --> 00:10:52.824
See ya.

202
00:10:54.827 --> 00:10:56.948
- I'm so glad you're back.
- Me. too.

203
00:10:57.388 --> 00:10:59.284
- How are you?
- Better now.

204
00:11:00.036 --> 00:11:02.133
I'll hook up with you later. okay?

205
00:11:06.042 --> 00:11:08.840
Nice view.
I can't tell what's cuter...

206
00:11:09.629 --> 00:11:11.843
The fact that Lucas has no
idea Lindsay's hitting on him.

207
00:11:11.968 --> 00:11:13.882
or that he's too into me to see it.

208
00:11:15.235 --> 00:11:17.735
The board's waiting for
you in the conference room.

209
00:11:19.096 --> 00:11:22.265
I'm having dinner with Jim. and I forgot
to make reservations. Could you?

210
00:11:22.897 --> 00:11:24.189
- Someplace...
- Romantic.

211
00:11:24.314 --> 00:11:26.749
Where they won't give the table
away if I'm late.

212
00:11:26.874 --> 00:11:29.230
But amid the untold
natural resources

213
00:11:29.398 --> 00:11:32.192
of the Amazon basin. we
have uncovered perhaps

214
00:11:32.705 --> 00:11:35.654
the crown jewel...
the trilsetum coronis.

215
00:11:37.239 --> 00:11:38.151
A plant?

216
00:11:39.599 --> 00:11:41.701
You're wasting the
board's time on a plant?

217
00:11:43.199 --> 00:11:46.077
Carbon-14 dating traces
the trilsetum coronis

218
00:11:46.202 --> 00:11:49.167
back to the Pleistocene epoch.
and as we know. that was the...

219
00:11:49.335 --> 00:11:52.045
I stand corrected. You're wasting
the board's time on a really old plant.

220
00:11:52.213 --> 00:11:55.131
Dr. Chiles... You'll get your turn to
waste the board's time.

221
00:11:55.299 --> 00:11:57.801
Indeed.
Continue. Dr. Powell.

222
00:11:59.439 --> 00:12:01.846
Our facilities in belém
are already experimenting

223
00:12:02.014 --> 00:12:04.796
with practical applicatis
across our divisions...

224
00:12:04.921 --> 00:12:07.268
pharmaceuticals. papers. green fuel.

225
00:12:07.436 --> 00:12:10.563
I'd bet money there is
nothing this plant can't do.

226
00:12:11.901 --> 00:12:14.192
I wanna buy out the whole place.
One hour.

227
00:12:14.360 --> 00:12:18.029
- And I want you to take a break.
- I'm not allowed to leave you here...

228
00:12:20.503 --> 00:12:22.367
For more than an hour.

229
00:12:59.675 --> 00:13:01.030
Come on.

230
00:13:45.622 --> 00:13:47.410
- Dr. King.
- Stephanie.

231
00:13:47.578 --> 00:13:50.448
- I've been looking for you.
- Sorry. I had to...

232
00:13:51.677 --> 00:13:54.015
- Step out for a second.
- No. No need to be defensive.

233
00:13:54.140 --> 00:13:55.752
I'm not that much of a taskmaster?

234
00:13:56.676 --> 00:13:58.630
Don't answer that.
At least not honestly.

235
00:13:59.168 --> 00:14:02.105
No. the reason I was looking for you
is I have some good news.

236
00:14:03.260 --> 00:14:04.636
The chairman's intrigued.

237
00:14:04.804 --> 00:14:06.242
- By?
- You.

238
00:14:06.597 --> 00:14:08.848
Your very old plant. specifically.

239
00:14:10.559 --> 00:14:12.275
He's flying in tonight.

240
00:14:13.229 --> 00:14:15.438
wants an in-depth
presentation over drinks.

241
00:14:16.416 --> 00:14:17.268
Drinks?

242
00:14:18.354 --> 00:14:20.610
A social custom commonly
enjoyed between adults.

243
00:14:22.606 --> 00:14:24.072
He wants to fund your research.

244
00:14:27.066 --> 00:14:29.243
Don't fracture anything
jumping for joy.

245
00:14:31.288 --> 00:14:33.373
- Can't wait.
- We'll leave from here.

246
00:14:40.876 --> 00:14:42.840
If this is a surprise party.

247
00:14:43.008 --> 00:14:45.093
I'd say that the
turnout's a bit depressing

248
00:14:45.653 --> 00:14:48.673
It's something I got to show you.
Watch this.

249
00:14:51.684 --> 00:14:53.931
You know. I'm no hideki matsui.

250
00:14:54.056 --> 00:14:57.025
but it might be a little easier
if you actually used a bat.

251
00:15:04.938 --> 00:15:07.949
Oh. you've been taking magic classes
at the learning annex?

252
00:15:08.117 --> 00:15:09.450
It's not magic classes.

253
00:15:11.386 --> 00:15:13.788
I think we're stepping over the line.
Where did you get that?

254
00:15:13.956 --> 00:15:16.749
Precinct supply closet.
Surprisingly poor lock.

255
00:15:16.917 --> 00:15:19.335
- What do you need that for?
- I don't. You do.

256
00:15:20.809 --> 00:15:22.422
I need you to shoot me.

257
00:15:32.919 --> 00:15:35.560
Date night's
not looking so promising.

258
00:15:35.728 --> 00:15:37.895
- Chairman's in town. and he...
- No. that's fine.

259
00:15:42.547 --> 00:15:44.882
I will get home as soon as I can.

260
00:15:45.007 --> 00:15:47.035
We'll grab some takeout.
light some candles.

261
00:15:47.160 --> 00:15:49.282
- and still have our night.
- Absolutely.

262
00:15:53.078 --> 00:15:56.086
- Let's do this.
- I can't believe I'm gonna kill you.

263
00:15:56.211 --> 00:15:57.752
You're not gonna kill me. George.

264
00:15:57.877 --> 00:16:01.345
- You're just gonna shoot me.
- I am a D.A.. and according to the law.

265
00:16:01.470 --> 00:16:04.264
- kinda the same thing.
- I told you. I did this yesterday.

266
00:16:04.389 --> 00:16:07.209
- I have to see if I can do it again.
- What if you can't?

267
00:16:07.334 --> 00:16:08.949
Where does that leave us?

268
00:16:09.074 --> 00:16:12.388
You dead and me showering with a bunch
of guys I wish I hadn't put away.

269
00:16:12.556 --> 00:16:15.027
Something extra ordinary's
happening to me.

270
00:16:15.152 --> 00:16:17.185
Something impossible.

271
00:16:17.860 --> 00:16:21.189
I need your help to
figure out what it is.

272
00:16:21.961 --> 00:16:23.109
Please?

273
00:16:32.048 --> 00:16:33.201
Just aim...

274
00:16:33.601 --> 00:16:34.434
And fire.

275
00:16:42.575 --> 00:16:43.723
I'm not...

276
00:16:56.488 --> 00:16:59.103
Dr. Powell.
Dr. King left a message...

277
00:16:59.228 --> 00:17:01.492
Said to meet them at
the chairman's hotel.

278
00:17:01.617 --> 00:17:03.494
And I'd take
the freeway if I were you.

279
00:17:03.619 --> 00:17:05.358
Streets are a mess this time of day.

280
00:17:10.656 --> 00:17:12.323
And that's when it happened.

281
00:17:12.957 --> 00:17:16.661
In the world of science. we call it
an unexplained phenomenon.

282
00:17:19.415 --> 00:17:20.581
An occurrence so...

283
00:17:21.064 --> 00:17:22.638
Random and bizarre.

284
00:17:23.692 --> 00:17:25.253
it defies explanation.

285
00:17:53.236 --> 00:17:55.867
And in a life short on time.

286
00:17:56.217 --> 00:17:58.051
i suddenly found myself...

287
00:17:59.032 --> 00:17:59.844
Fast.

288
00:18:17.223 --> 00:18:20.225
For the next few weeks. I did my best
to act as if nothing had changed.

289
00:18:20.393 --> 00:18:22.477
I'd kiss my family good-bye.

290
00:18:23.062 --> 00:18:25.105
counting the minutes
till I could meet George

291
00:18:25.540 --> 00:18:27.927
to write the owner's
manual for my new ride.

292
00:18:28.052 --> 00:18:30.186
- Most of them can fly.
- I can't fly.

293
00:18:30.403 --> 00:18:33.488
- How many can catch bullets even?
- I can't fly.

294
00:18:33.656 --> 00:18:35.600
Just take a running jump.

295
00:18:36.739 --> 00:18:38.855
Get a head of steam. all right?

296
00:18:38.980 --> 00:18:41.874
And you just think like
something that can fly.

297
00:18:44.375 --> 00:18:47.544
That's easy for you to say.
but if this doesn't work. I'm road kill.

298
00:18:47.712 --> 00:18:50.547
From the guy that begged me to
shoot him the other day. Huh.

299
00:18:54.965 --> 00:18:56.095
All right.

300
00:19:29.921 --> 00:19:30.962
You can't fly!

301
00:19:40.812 --> 00:19:41.765
George!

302
00:19:51.454 --> 00:19:52.726
But you can jump.

303
00:19:54.320 --> 00:19:55.422
You can jump!

304
00:19:57.971 --> 00:19:59.935
<i>I wasn't sure what was happening
with Jim.</i>

305
00:20:00.060 --> 00:20:00.961
You all right?

306
00:20:01.086 --> 00:20:03.492
But I had to share my new abilities
with someone...

307
00:20:03.961 --> 00:20:04.805
a peer.

308
00:20:05.361 --> 00:20:07.624
<i>Someone who had
the scientific capacity</i>

309
00:20:07.834 --> 00:20:09.818
<i>to understand
what was happening to me.</i>

310
00:20:10.215 --> 00:20:11.795
Can I talk to you in confidence?

311
00:20:11.963 --> 00:20:14.464
My God. You're firing me.
Are you firing me?

312
00:20:14.888 --> 00:20:17.198
<i>Admittedly.
I might have chosen better.</i>

313
00:20:18.808 --> 00:20:19.949
I'm not firing you.

314
00:20:20.074 --> 00:20:21.388
- Good.
- This is about me.

315
00:20:23.160 --> 00:20:25.613
Are you gonna tell me something
personal like we're best friends.

316
00:20:25.738 --> 00:20:28.130
even though I'm just your lab tech?
'Cause that would validate

317
00:20:28.255 --> 00:20:30.186
everything I've been
working on in therapy.

318
00:20:31.448 --> 00:20:33.483
You know that superhero thingy
you keep

319
00:20:33.651 --> 00:20:35.905
- in your cubicle downstairs?
- Kitty Pryde.

320
00:20:36.404 --> 00:20:38.655
She's my favorite x-man.
X-woman. technically.

321
00:20:41.387 --> 00:20:42.393
I'm fast.

322
00:20:48.704 --> 00:20:50.238
I can't believe I'm here...

323
00:20:54.589 --> 00:20:55.505
doing this.

324
00:20:56.632 --> 00:20:57.924
Accepting this.

325
00:20:59.788 --> 00:21:02.194
How does your body cut
through the wind shear?

326
00:21:05.328 --> 00:21:08.530
Why doesn't the coulomb
friction singe your clothes!

327
00:21:09.937 --> 00:21:11.896
Are you generating some
kind of charged

328
00:21:12.277 --> 00:21:14.315
plasma field
from the kinetic energy?

329
00:21:16.777 --> 00:21:19.075
Is that why incoming
debris isn't sandblasting

330
00:21:19.200 --> 00:21:20.494
off your corneas?

331
00:21:26.303 --> 00:21:27.162
How'd I do?

332
00:21:27.330 --> 00:21:29.622
You are doing a mile
every 6 seconds.

333
00:21:30.812 --> 00:21:32.459
I thought I was faster than that.

334
00:21:33.448 --> 00:21:36.051
My God! The Olympics.
You should totally enter.

335
00:21:36.176 --> 00:21:38.339
Where are they this year?
Korea? They're always in Korea.

336
00:21:39.250 --> 00:21:40.925
I'm not interested in the Olympics.

337
00:21:41.545 --> 00:21:43.720
- What are you interested in?
- Making time.

338
00:21:44.086 --> 00:21:46.212
Thanks to your increased
metabolic rate.

339
00:21:46.337 --> 00:21:48.811
your life is like a
never-ending spin class.

340
00:21:49.233 --> 00:21:52.654
So despite the need for
massive caloric intake.

341
00:21:53.405 --> 00:21:55.964
you're gonna be a size zero
for the rest of your life.

342
00:21:56.798 --> 00:21:58.514
- I hate you.
- My gosh.

343
00:21:58.639 --> 00:21:59.961
It's already 3:00.

344
00:22:00.086 --> 00:22:01.121
I've gotta.

345
00:22:01.246 --> 00:22:02.012
well.

346
00:22:02.137 --> 00:22:02.923
run.

347
00:22:07.586 --> 00:22:08.344
Mom.

348
00:22:08.775 --> 00:22:10.371
What are you doing down here?

349
00:22:10.496 --> 00:22:12.173
I told you I would make some time

350
00:22:12.298 --> 00:22:14.834
to help with your schoolwork.
What do we have here?

351
00:22:15.945 --> 00:22:16.769
Math.

352
00:22:17.498 --> 00:22:20.939
"If a bullet train leaves New York
going 350 miles per hour..."

353
00:22:23.220 --> 00:22:25.095
I think I can help you on this one.

354
00:22:25.474 --> 00:22:26.845
Here's what we know so far.

355
00:22:26.970 --> 00:22:29.298
You can jump just over
a quarter mile in a single leap.

356
00:22:29.423 --> 00:22:30.564
A single what?

357
00:22:32.120 --> 00:22:33.481
Fine. Single bound.

358
00:22:34.211 --> 00:22:35.984
No discernible increase
in foot speed.

359
00:22:36.109 --> 00:22:38.191
However.
you can lift just in the area of

360
00:22:38.359 --> 00:22:39.703
11.000 pounds...

361
00:22:40.163 --> 00:22:41.831
And you can catch bullets.

362
00:22:42.326 --> 00:22:45.364
Have you. talked to Steph about this.
tell her what you can do?

363
00:22:47.674 --> 00:22:48.880
She's your wife.

364
00:22:49.319 --> 00:22:52.254
You have to bring her into this cone
of silence. What is that?

365
00:22:54.368 --> 00:22:56.164
What are you doing
with a police scanner?

366
00:22:56.289 --> 00:22:59.237
I have these abilities. I should be
using them for something. right?

367
00:22:59.362 --> 00:23:01.997
Like... stopping these
psychos in Obama masks.

368
00:23:02.122 --> 00:23:03.716
- killing innocent people.
- Hold on.

369
00:23:03.884 --> 00:23:06.815
All we have learned so far is that
we have a lot to learn.

370
00:23:07.163 --> 00:23:08.898
You're special.
but you're not invincible.

371
00:23:09.023 --> 00:23:10.515
I don't know if you're vincible.

372
00:23:10.767 --> 00:23:13.268
- Hold on. It's Stephanie.
- Tell her.

373
00:23:13.436 --> 00:23:14.212
Hello?

374
00:23:16.158 --> 00:23:18.923
I finished work.
I tutored J.J.. and...

375
00:23:19.317 --> 00:23:22.193
- It isn't even 4:00 yet.
- And I can jump a quarter of a mile.

376
00:23:22.470 --> 00:23:24.920
I'm... moving kind of fast today.

377
00:23:25.610 --> 00:23:27.456
Anyway. the kids aren't here. and...

378
00:23:28.099 --> 00:23:31.108
Remember what we'd do sometimes
when we both had a free afternoon?

379
00:23:34.391 --> 00:23:36.892
It's nice to remember
we're good at that.

380
00:23:38.809 --> 00:23:41.109
That's a nice thing to be good at.

381
00:23:43.600 --> 00:23:45.201
You seem different to me.

382
00:23:47.473 --> 00:23:48.260
Me?

383
00:23:51.030 --> 00:23:52.637
I thought that about you.

384
00:23:54.560 --> 00:23:55.626
You have?

385
00:23:55.952 --> 00:23:57.859
Jim. how could I not notice?

386
00:23:58.904 --> 00:23:59.939
You seem...

387
00:24:02.216 --> 00:24:03.031
Happy.

388
00:24:05.671 --> 00:24:06.495
What?

389
00:24:07.531 --> 00:24:10.048
My life wasn't turning
out the way I'd hoped.

390
00:24:10.470 --> 00:24:13.536
Meanwhile. you were running around.
living your dreams.

391
00:24:14.846 --> 00:24:15.668
I was

392
00:24:15.793 --> 00:24:16.847
running...

393
00:24:17.345 --> 00:24:19.818
so much that I was falling
short at everything.

394
00:24:19.943 --> 00:24:21.170
Falling short?

395
00:24:21.639 --> 00:24:22.579
Honey...

396
00:24:23.499 --> 00:24:25.006
Who could keep up with you?

397
00:24:25.709 --> 00:24:27.769
You couldn't.
because you stopped trying.

398
00:24:38.946 --> 00:24:40.498
We both stopped trying.

399
00:24:45.584 --> 00:24:47.737
You wanna know what's going on
with your daughter?

400
00:24:49.965 --> 00:24:52.116
She's afraid she's gonna lose
her boyfriend

401
00:24:52.284 --> 00:24:53.820
to a girl that'll sleep with him

402
00:24:54.367 --> 00:24:56.245
because she's not ready to yet.

403
00:24:57.290 --> 00:24:58.414
And J.J....

404
00:24:58.888 --> 00:25:00.576
he's struggling with school

405
00:25:00.701 --> 00:25:03.221
because the school wants to
put him in remedial classes.

406
00:25:03.346 --> 00:25:07.123
But you won't accept the fact
that your son has a learning disability.

407
00:25:09.377 --> 00:25:11.025
Now you may have known
all these things

408
00:25:11.150 --> 00:25:13.301
if you were home for more
than 20 minutes a night.

409
00:25:16.163 --> 00:25:17.869
I guess it's the dream of everyone

410
00:25:17.994 --> 00:25:20.327
to work 80 hours a week
to support a family.

411
00:25:28.756 --> 00:25:31.032
Guess what? You got your wish.

412
00:25:31.157 --> 00:25:33.866
Obama mask.
Robbery in progress. You're on.

413
00:25:35.274 --> 00:25:36.369
<i>Okay. Perp...</i>

414
00:25:37.073 --> 00:25:38.454
"Perp". I like that.

415
00:25:39.081 --> 00:25:42.083
Perp headed north on 12th and fig.

416
00:25:47.106 --> 00:25:48.256
I have to go.

417
00:26:05.720 --> 00:26:08.484
I'm on top of the Simonson building
heading north. Which way now?

418
00:26:11.180 --> 00:26:12.023
It's a left.

419
00:26:12.148 --> 00:26:14.141
Are you sure you don't wanna use
the freeway route?

420
00:26:14.266 --> 00:26:17.156
- 'Cause it looks much faster.
- I'm not worried about traffic.

421
00:27:02.164 --> 00:27:03.664
You're going away for a long time.

422
00:27:28.107 --> 00:27:29.315
Help me. George.

423
00:27:29.995 --> 00:27:31.213
I've been shot.

424
00:27:41.623 --> 00:27:42.696
You're awake.

425
00:27:42.954 --> 00:27:45.415
You had some blood loss.
but the bullet didn't penetrate too far.

426
00:27:45.583 --> 00:27:47.344
- We sewed you up...
- "We"?

427
00:27:48.242 --> 00:27:49.711
- No.
- Do tell me.

428
00:27:49.879 --> 00:27:52.130
Where was I supposed to take you.
to the hospital?

429
00:27:52.298 --> 00:27:53.923
And explain
why a large-caliber bullet

430
00:27:54.048 --> 00:27:56.177
only penetrated a quarter of an inch
through your scalp?

431
00:27:56.302 --> 00:27:58.638
But she'll never understand
what's happening to me.

432
00:27:59.184 --> 00:28:01.082
I think you'll be surprised.

433
00:28:04.456 --> 00:28:06.311
Remember the sketch of me
in your studio?

434
00:28:06.558 --> 00:28:08.188
The one you Drew on our first date?

435
00:28:16.072 --> 00:28:17.553
You two are freaky.

436
00:28:19.404 --> 00:28:20.324
But how?

437
00:28:23.793 --> 00:28:26.873
I've been racking my brain.
and the only possible variable...

438
00:28:27.154 --> 00:28:29.376
- Plane crash.
- It's the only explanation.

439
00:28:30.319 --> 00:28:32.212
And when our plane went down.

440
00:28:32.380 --> 00:28:33.854
<i>the water had a...</i>

441
00:28:34.305 --> 00:28:35.507
<i>phosphorescence.</i>

442
00:28:35.675 --> 00:28:38.260
<i>At the time. I thought
it was gasoline from the plane.</i>

443
00:28:38.992 --> 00:28:40.971
<i>But gas floats on water.</i>

444
00:28:41.690 --> 00:28:42.658
<i>This didn't.</i>

445
00:28:43.016 --> 00:28:46.226
It's the only thing that makes sense
if any of this makes any sense.

446
00:28:47.886 --> 00:28:49.896
But... we were all in the water.

447
00:28:56.152 --> 00:28:57.015
Hello?

448
00:28:57.697 --> 00:28:58.530
Daphne?

449
00:28:58.989 --> 00:29:00.907
Calm down. honey. Where are you?

450
00:29:02.698 --> 00:29:04.369
I called dad.

451
00:29:05.809 --> 00:29:07.957
He has a headache.

452
00:29:08.349 --> 00:29:09.725
He's home resting.

453
00:29:10.259 --> 00:29:12.502
I usually talk to
him about this sort of thing.

454
00:29:13.093 --> 00:29:14.254
I know.

455
00:29:16.223 --> 00:29:19.092
Before the game.
I was on the court

456
00:29:19.260 --> 00:29:20.802
with Emily.

457
00:29:23.970 --> 00:29:25.640
Are you not gonna
say something to her?

458
00:29:26.559 --> 00:29:29.544
She was all over Lucas the entire time
you were in Mexico.

459
00:29:30.051 --> 00:29:31.181
Or wherever.

460
00:29:32.148 --> 00:29:34.399
This is a boyfriend problem?

461
00:29:34.567 --> 00:29:35.275
Wait.

462
00:29:35.847 --> 00:29:38.653
- Stay away from Lucas.
- He was talking to me.

463
00:29:38.821 --> 00:29:40.990
It took me a year
to get Lucas to notice me.

464
00:29:41.407 --> 00:29:43.533
Maybe if weren't so concerned
with losing Lucas.

465
00:29:43.701 --> 00:29:46.286
- you'd notice that you already have.
- What do you mean?

466
00:29:46.638 --> 00:29:49.517
<i>You're so clueless. I can't believe I
actually feel bad for you.</i>

467
00:29:53.318 --> 00:29:54.970
Bad for me? Why?

468
00:29:56.226 --> 00:29:57.756
I didn't say anything.

469
00:30:03.105 --> 00:30:04.262
Then the game started.

470
00:30:04.430 --> 00:30:06.681
<i>She's not gonna pass.
She never passes to me.</i>

471
00:30:10.853 --> 00:30:12.646
<i>This game blows. I need a drink.</i>

472
00:30:18.945 --> 00:30:20.654
I wasn't hearing my thoughts.

473
00:30:21.108 --> 00:30:22.364
I was hearing theirs.

474
00:30:23.422 --> 00:30:25.283
You probably think I'm
losing my mind.

475
00:30:25.451 --> 00:30:28.328
No. no. I actually believe
every word.

476
00:30:29.580 --> 00:30:31.873
There's something
I need to tell you.

477
00:30:32.528 --> 00:30:35.502
Something extraordinary
has happened...

478
00:30:35.670 --> 00:30:37.837
is happening to us.

479
00:30:38.620 --> 00:30:41.716
and you may be
experiencing things. too.

480
00:30:41.884 --> 00:30:44.177
that you don't even
understand entirely.

481
00:30:45.375 --> 00:30:47.722
- J.J.?
- This is unbelievable.

482
00:30:48.235 --> 00:30:50.809
My whole family gets
dipped in some super water.

483
00:30:50.977 --> 00:30:52.936
and all I get... is wet.

484
00:30:53.104 --> 00:30:54.887
So you haven't been...

485
00:30:55.012 --> 00:30:58.208
No. dad. I haven't.
I am still plain old J.J...

486
00:30:59.159 --> 00:31:01.027
- The dumb one.
- Don't say that. kiddo.

487
00:31:01.152 --> 00:31:03.678
- It's true.
- Can we just stop talking about this?

488
00:31:04.991 --> 00:31:07.200
You're telepathic.
We should talk about it.

489
00:31:07.368 --> 00:31:09.679
It happened to me only once.

490
00:31:09.804 --> 00:31:11.997
so as far as I'm concerned.
I'm in the same boat as J.J.

491
00:31:12.937 --> 00:31:15.011
just as boring as I was last week.

492
00:31:15.136 --> 00:31:17.752
Daphne. I can help you. The
more we begin to understand

493
00:31:17.920 --> 00:31:20.205
- about our abilities...
- I don't want new abilities!

494
00:31:20.330 --> 00:31:22.215
High School is hard enough as it is!

495
00:31:22.546 --> 00:31:24.768
Why are we having
this meeting anyway?

496
00:31:25.379 --> 00:31:27.554
So you two can convince yourselves
that you're different?

497
00:31:28.287 --> 00:31:30.765
'Cause you can catch bullets
and you can run fast?

498
00:31:30.933 --> 00:31:32.100
That's enough.

499
00:31:32.268 --> 00:31:34.046
We go on vacations to reconnect.

500
00:31:34.528 --> 00:31:36.824
Why would we wanna
connect in the first place?

501
00:31:37.342 --> 00:31:39.528
To watch mom stress about work?

502
00:31:39.859 --> 00:31:42.996
Or watch dad mope around like
he lost a winning lottery ticket?

503
00:31:43.121 --> 00:31:44.904
Even J.J.. that idot. can see it!

504
00:31:45.072 --> 00:31:47.806
That's it!
Go to your room right now!

505
00:31:48.191 --> 00:31:50.603
All the trips and all the
talks couldn't save this family

506
00:31:50.728 --> 00:31:52.927
because this family isn't broken!

507
00:31:53.052 --> 00:31:54.315
You two are!

508
00:32:05.265 --> 00:32:06.676
She's right. isn't she?

509
00:32:24.268 --> 00:32:25.953
What's this?

510
00:32:26.078 --> 00:32:28.114
We got lucky here. Witness saw

511
00:32:28.282 --> 00:32:30.448
- this guy fleeing at police pursuit.
- I haven't heard.

512
00:32:30.573 --> 00:32:32.243
I already run him.

513
00:32:32.535 --> 00:32:35.371
Guy's name is Reed Koblenz.

514
00:32:36.083 --> 00:32:37.999
He jump here last month
from Michigan.

515
00:32:38.124 --> 00:32:40.836
And this woman named Sally Down
is supposed to???

516
00:32:41.541 --> 00:32:44.041
We got a lead.
Nice work. pal!

517
00:32:47.260 --> 00:32:48.510
Having trouble say goodbye.

518
00:32:48.874 --> 00:32:52.485
I thought I just taggle on.
As backup?

519
00:32:52.610 --> 00:32:55.809
I like the enthusiasm. Leave the crime
fight to the one of us with guns.

520
00:33:13.468 --> 00:33:15.654
I don't know what's going on off
on the yard now.

521
00:33:15.779 --> 00:33:17.827
Still all of us.

522
00:33:19.169 --> 00:33:20.966
What's wrong.

523
00:33:22.957 --> 00:33:24.198
I'll be fine.

524
00:33:25.307 --> 00:33:28.550
Probably some post traumatic stress
from the crash.

525
00:33:30.136 --> 00:33:32.696
I really glad I came here.

526
00:33:38.484 --> 00:33:40.077
Feel nice.

527
00:33:40.202 --> 00:33:42.856
<i>I need to get out here.
I supposed to meet Emily in an hour.</i>

528
00:33:43.929 --> 00:33:45.854
- What?
- I didn't say anything.

529
00:33:46.945 --> 00:33:48.361
Emily. my best friend?

530
00:33:49.188 --> 00:33:52.115
- What about her?
- You supposed to meet up with her.

531
00:33:52.892 --> 00:33:54.743
No. What you mean?

532
00:33:54.911 --> 00:33:56.459
<i>How did she know that?</i>

533
00:33:57.626 --> 00:33:59.552
Why are you seeing Emily?

534
00:34:00.452 --> 00:34:02.209
Did Emily tell to her?

535
00:34:03.581 --> 00:34:05.003
You're sleeping with her!

536
00:34:05.171 --> 00:34:07.130
She's like your best friend!

537
00:34:07.581 --> 00:34:08.617
Not that...

538
00:34:08.742 --> 00:34:11.843
I'm so stupid!
You said you were okay to wait.

539
00:34:12.444 --> 00:34:15.305
I am. Of course I am.

540
00:34:15.473 --> 00:34:18.850
Thanks for telling me
how you really feel.

541
00:34:20.144 --> 00:34:22.395
I appreciate your honesty.

542
00:34:23.039 --> 00:34:24.455
Come on. Daph.

543
00:34:25.191 --> 00:34:27.901
How the hell did she know all that?

544
00:34:29.821 --> 00:34:33.140
Ms. Downs. I'm Detective Cho.
This is Detective Hixon.

545
00:34:33.265 --> 00:34:35.742
If it's not too much trouble.
we'd like to ask you a few questions.

546
00:34:35.910 --> 00:34:38.203
- About?
- Your former boyfriend. Reed Koblenz.

547
00:34:38.371 --> 00:34:40.997
Reed? I haven't seen him
since I posted his bail.

548
00:34:41.165 --> 00:34:43.462
If you find him.
tell him he owes me 2 grand.

549
00:34:46.167 --> 00:34:48.963
If he attempts any
contact. please let us know.

550
00:34:54.336 --> 00:34:55.095
Koblenz?

551
00:35:05.514 --> 00:35:07.891
Pack everything up. then disappear.

552
00:35:08.109 --> 00:35:10.110
This one is my insurance policy.

553
00:35:15.746 --> 00:35:18.485
Remembering when
we used to be normal?

554
00:35:19.734 --> 00:35:22.679
- You okay?
- I'm fine. Just... wanna be alone.

555
00:35:23.605 --> 00:35:26.539
I know I haven't always
been there for you. but...

556
00:35:29.390 --> 00:35:30.839
I'm here now.

557
00:35:35.608 --> 00:35:36.803
Did it happen again?

558
00:35:39.910 --> 00:35:41.410
I was with Lucas.

559
00:35:43.735 --> 00:35:46.396
And when I looked in his eyes.
I could read his thoughts.

560
00:35:48.482 --> 00:35:50.389
He's sleeping with Emily.

561
00:35:56.841 --> 00:35:59.656
- That bitch.
- I know. right?

562
00:36:01.470 --> 00:36:05.206
And he said he loved me...
That he would wait for me.

563
00:36:07.359 --> 00:36:09.461
Why would he say it
if it wasn't true?

564
00:36:11.297 --> 00:36:14.575
It's not fair. I can't
be a virgin and a freak.

565
00:36:17.061 --> 00:36:18.094
What's going on?

566
00:36:18.704 --> 00:36:21.749
Talking about your new
cool powers.

567
00:36:21.874 --> 00:36:23.751
Keep me updated
on the costume design.

568
00:36:23.876 --> 00:36:25.268
J.J.. stop.

569
00:36:28.074 --> 00:36:30.065
We're a family no
matter what happens to us

570
00:36:30.543 --> 00:36:32.442
or what doesn't happen to us.

571
00:36:32.610 --> 00:36:34.861
Nothing's gonna change
that. You understand?

572
00:36:38.816 --> 00:36:41.952
I think I liked us better
when we were just dysfunctional.

573
00:36:50.837 --> 00:36:52.087
Let her go.

574
00:36:54.603 --> 00:36:56.116
If I let her go.

575
00:36:56.241 --> 00:36:58.635
she wouldn't make a very
good hostage. now would she?

576
00:36:58.803 --> 00:37:00.080
I'm warning you.

577
00:37:00.205 --> 00:37:02.543
You don't have a partner
here this time to stop me.

578
00:37:03.649 --> 00:37:05.475
Who says I ever did?

579
00:37:06.727 --> 00:37:08.520
You thought you were the only one.

580
00:37:37.902 --> 00:37:40.719
Last time we met. I didn't kill you.

581
00:37:40.887 --> 00:37:42.846
But then again. I shot
you from 4 feet away.

582
00:37:43.532 --> 00:37:47.292
Don't you know?
You and me. we are not alone...

583
00:37:54.844 --> 00:37:57.850
What are you doing here. Powell?
Trying to be some sort of hero? I...

584
00:37:59.030 --> 00:38:02.657
Get outta here now. before you're
answering questions from I.A.

585
00:38:22.674 --> 00:38:23.928
I'm home.

586
00:38:25.697 --> 00:38:26.997
Jim?

587
00:38:29.412 --> 00:38:30.709
We need to talk.

588
00:38:38.754 --> 00:38:40.737
You may have felt like
you couldn't keep up.

589
00:38:42.609 --> 00:38:45.572
but while I was racing
to be the perfect spouse.

590
00:38:45.961 --> 00:38:47.331
the perfect parent...

591
00:38:49.132 --> 00:38:50.580
You were it.

592
00:38:55.912 --> 00:38:58.671
You were extraordinary before
you could ever catch a bullet.

593
00:39:01.667 --> 00:39:05.058
Maybe it's taken something crazy
to make us thankful for what we have.

594
00:39:07.873 --> 00:39:09.057
Promise me.

595
00:39:11.494 --> 00:39:13.478
No more bullets.
No more crime fighting.

596
00:39:15.274 --> 00:39:18.316
'Cause in a way. I feel like
I'm just getting you back.

597
00:39:22.297 --> 00:39:23.196
I promise.

598
00:39:32.898 --> 00:39:36.765
You have 20 minutes to solve
the equation I've written on the board.

599
00:39:36.890 --> 00:39:39.921
Solve for "x" and make
sure you show all your work.

600
00:39:40.089 --> 00:39:42.368
- Dude. you study for this?
- Why bother?

601
00:39:42.782 --> 00:39:43.967
You may begin now.

602
00:40:23.883 --> 00:40:26.898
What are you doing. man?

603
00:40:30.602 --> 00:40:32.390
What did you do?

604
00:40:32.558 --> 00:40:34.713
You've got a new hobby now.

605
00:40:34.838 --> 00:40:38.567
My brother knows a guy.
You need blu-ray anything...

606
00:40:38.692 --> 00:40:41.257
- So you turned your garage into...
- That's right.

607
00:40:41.382 --> 00:40:43.193
What every secret
crime fighter needs...

608
00:40:44.487 --> 00:40:47.530
a lair... with Wi-Fi.

609
00:40:48.622 --> 00:40:51.618
I have a lair... With Wi-Fi.

610
00:40:57.199 --> 00:40:59.076
I know it's quite a story.

611
00:40:59.201 --> 00:41:01.917
but you asked us how
we got here. so...

612
00:41:04.158 --> 00:41:05.899
Did I leave anything out?

613
00:41:06.024 --> 00:41:07.926
No. I think you hit
all the highlights.

614
00:41:09.473 --> 00:41:10.418
So?

615
00:41:12.566 --> 00:41:15.049
What do you think. Dr. Allen?

616
00:41:16.232 --> 00:41:17.393
I think...

617
00:41:17.973 --> 00:41:20.730
We've...
got our work cut out for us.

618
00:41:21.214 --> 00:41:22.732
Might suggest we start with...

619
00:41:22.900 --> 00:41:24.400
Twice a week?

620
00:41:25.770 --> 00:41:28.863
- Sure.
- Sounds great. We want this to work.

621
00:41:29.031 --> 00:41:32.352
not just for us but...
for our family.

622
00:41:38.649 --> 00:41:41.000
The problems we face
may no longer be ordinary.

623
00:41:44.260 --> 00:41:45.667
but then again...

624
00:41:47.866 --> 00:41:49.273
Neither are we.

625
00:42:17.977 --> 00:42:20.373
I see you've found Koblenz.

626
00:42:22.181 --> 00:42:24.836
Find out who knows about him.

627
00:42:25.433 --> 00:42:27.297
And then take care of it.
